You can adjust the `Comparator` to whatever you need. Reasonable choices could be the `name` of the enum or the `ordinal`. Alternatively you could also overwrite `toString()` and use that to sort the Enums or you could even assign the enum and attribute `key` and sort it using that.

Here how you would sort the `List` using the the enum value name.
```java
import java.util.*;

public class Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
